I always have one ear on the unique strengths of the Artist and the other ear on what's trending in the current market. You can’t afford to ignore either. I've produced thousands of songs and what that experience has taught me is how to connect an Artist with an audience. There are often five different ways I could produce a song, but usually, only one way that perfectly elevates the Artist. That’s the key to standing out and it's paramount for an Artist’s success.

Sal Oliveri
Record Producer • Artist Development

We all have to start somewhere. For me, it was my dad's basement in Rahway, NJ. 

This is my first business card that I handed out to anyone who would take one. I had no idea what was ahead but I was determined to keep growing and would take every opportunity… small or lar... well… they were all small at the beginning. As my skills and experience grew, so did the opportunities. 

Many years later, I’ve been involved in so many amazing Artists’ careers that I just laugh in amazement when I look at this card. At that time I could only dream of doing half of what I’ve been able to do. It seemed almost impossible and out of reach. 

Maybe you feel that way sometimes. The truth is that most people overestimate what they can do in 1 year, but underestimate what they can do in 5, 10 or more.  Stay humble, always treat others well and keep investing in yourself. It’ll pay off.

.
.
.

Amazing Story:
1. Nov 2017 I get a sense that I should make a music project for people struggling w/ anxiety, depression or just wanting more Peace in their life.
2. I follow thru for the next month writing and recording what became, "Piano Prayers". All the while, unsure what I would do with it or if anyone would even listen. 
3. Near the end of the recording, a new friend / client asked me what I've been working on lately. I tell her about it and the reason for it. She asks me to send her a copy when I'm done. 
4. Jan 2018 I complete the project, send her a copy, she calls saying how much she loved it. “Oh, that’s nice", I thought. 
5. Following Monday: she (@kathielgifford ) tells over 5 Million people about my "Piano Prayers" project on The @todayshow . 
6. A week later: The project went to #4 on the Billboard chart.
7. 5 years later: I'm still getting messages from people around the world thanking me for making this music and how much it helps them. 
8. Mind blown. 
9. God is amazing.
10. Lesson: Pay attention to that “gut feeling”... then put action to it.  #pianoprayers #piano #anxiety #stressrelief #peace #peaceofmind #nashville #recordproducer

I was the kid who read all the liner notes on every album. I made mental notes about ￼which studios, gear, engineers, and musicians were used. I fantasized about finding a way into those circles… even to just play a small role.￼￼ Little did I know that ￼I would end up being the one leading and directing a room full of world-class talent. I’ve been in this amazing position for so long that you might think the excitement wears off. It doesn’t!!

Just keep pressing forward. You never know where you might end up.

Sal Oliveri

One of the BEST pieces of gear I've acquired recently is the Solid State Logic (SSL) UC-1!! Besides their Channel Strip and Bus Comp sounding AMAZING... the tactile interface is a game changer for mixing ITB. It's so easy to fall into the trap of "listening with your eyes" when using plugins on a screen... this eliminates that for me because I can grab the knob and turn till my ears tell me what's right. - [ ] Several years ago, I did a guest lecture at Belmont to a group of young singer-songwriters. Afterward, one of the students reached out to me to listen to some of her songs. There was one in the batch that stood out to me. She asked if I’d consider producing it for her first release. She had enough money to do a simple demo, but I suggested that the song was worthy of a better recording. After saving, she returned, and we recorded her first single, “You Flew”. Her acoustic guitar part was a perfect foundation for her beautiful and chilling vocals. The rest was done by yours truly. I check up on her Spotify occasionally and was so happy to see her streaming reach over 630k on this song! That’s amazing as an independent Artist, especially on a first release! .

I used to think those were ‘special people’ on stage. They must have grown up somewhere different, eaten different food, and had other-worldly abilities.

After making it from the audience to the stage, I discovered the difference.
 
They weren’t ‘special’... they were ‘prepared.’ 

I share this picture once a year as a testimony that hard work and dedication pay off. Do the reps, put in the hours, focus on a goal, and don’t give up. Then when opportunity knocks, you’ll be prepared! Most importantly, don’t think you can get there all by yourself. You need the support of others and help from those who know the way there.
